The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, held a press briefing on March 9, 2009. During the briefing, he discussed various topics including the President's focus on the manipulation and coercion of scientific research, the meeting between the President and Chairman Bernanke, the upcoming G20 summit, Chinese vessels harassing U.S. ships, Warren Buffet's comments on cap and trade, the President's executive order on stem cell research, signing statements, and the progress of nominations to various agencies and departments. He also addressed the President's upcoming speech on education and the administration's approach to addressing multiple challenges simultaneously.